message.entry: Input class is not supported.
Comparison method must be ''auto'', ''abs'', or ''real''.
Specify comparison method last.
Mixed inputs must be either single and double or integer and scalar double. All other combinations are not allowed.
Two output arguments are not supported for two input arrays.
Specifying the operating dimension is not supported for two input arrays.
''linear'' option is not supported for two input arrays.
Invalid data type. Sparse integer and single input arrays are not supported.
Complex integer input array not supported.
Argument must be ''ComparisonMethod'' or missing value condition specified as ''omitmissing'', ''omitnan'', ''includemissing'', or ''includenan''.
Argument must be ''linear'', ''ComparisonMethod'', or missing value condition specified as ''omitmissing'', ''omitnan'', ''includemissing'', or ''includenan''.
Argument must be ''all'', ''linear'', ''ComparisonMethod'', or missing value condition specified as ''omitmissing'', ''omitnan'', ''includemissing'', or ''includenan''.
Invalid option combination. Specify only one missing value condition.
Invalid option combination. Specify ''linear'' only once.
Invalid second argument. To specify an option, use min(A,[],option).
First input array is an invalid data type.
Second input array is an invalid data type.
Invalid second argument. To specify an additional argument, use min(A,[],...).
Specify ''linear'' option when returning two outputs and the operating dimension is a vector.
Second output is not supported for sparse input arrays of this size.
''ComparisonMethod'' parameter supported only when input array is numeric or logical.
Invalid second argument. To specify the comparison method, use min(A,[],"ComparisonMethod",method).
Invalid second argument. To operate over all elements of the input array, use min(A,[],"all").
Incorrect number of input arguments. ''ComparisonMethod'' must be followed by a corresponding value.
Parameter name must be ''ComparisonMethod''.
